<subSubSection pageId="5" pageNumber="199" type="etymology">
<paragraph blockId="5.[151,1436,1268,1689]" pageId="5" pageNumber="199">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,334,1593,1617]" pageId="5" pageNumber="199">Etymology.</emphasis>
Noun compound of Greek derivation: 
<taxonomicName box="[786,962,1593,1617]" class="Insecta" family="Myrmeleontidae" genus="Megistoleon" kingdom="Animalia" order="Neuroptera" pageId="5" pageNumber="199" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="thaumatopteryx">
<emphasis box="[786,962,1593,1617]" italics="true" pageId="5" pageNumber="199">thaumatopteryx</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, “wonderful wing”, refers to the striking wing pattern.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection box="[199,1312,1664,1689]" pageId="5" pageNumber="199" type="distribution">
<paragraph blockId="5.[151,1436,1268,1689]" box="[199,1312,1664,1689]" pageId="5" pageNumber="199">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,352,1664,1689]" pageId="5" pageNumber="199">Distribution.</emphasis>
The new species is known only from the Mozambican 
<typeStatus box="[972,1020,1665,1689]" pageId="5" pageNumber="199">type</typeStatus>
locality, a lowland forest.
</paragraph>
